verses.text:
I love to climb where Jesus leads far from the Golden gloom;
Up, up the shining mountain steeds, beyond the veil of doom;
Where eagles soar and spirits soar, and angels come and go,
And Jesus waits with open door, and bids my soul to know.

I love to be with Jesus, where rolling mists depart;
Where I can see His loving face, and feel His beating heart;
Where I can lay my weary head upon His faithful breast,
And find in Him my all in all, my home, my hope, my rest.

I love to lift my eyes above the shadows dark and drear;
Where faith can reach and hope can move, and love can persevere;
Where sorrows flee and teardrops dry, and broken hearts find balm,
And Jesus reigns supremely nigh, and all is peace and calm.

I love to sit with Jesus where the glory round me falls;
Where I can hear the music there, and harken to His calls;
Where I can tell Him all my need, and know that He will care,
And He will give me all I need, and more than I can bear.

chorus.text:
On the mountain, on the mountain, where the golden sunlight gleams;
On the mountain, on the mountain, God is nearer than He seems;
On the mountain, on the mountain, I can see my Savior's face,
On the mountain, on the mountain, I can feel His wondrous grace.
